        dc:description           "FIG. 7. — Female of Centuriarus centurio (Brunner von Wattenwyl,1898) n. comb.: FW venation (A), apex of ovipositor (B), and copulatory papilla in ventral (C), lateral (D) and dorsal (E) views. In FW venation, dense dotted areas represent dark colouration patterns; in copulatory papilla, dotted parts correspond to membranous areas. Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4546749/files/figure.png" .

